WEBVTT

00:44.080 --> 00:45.570
Kenichi...

00:46.160 --> 00:47.360
Hideki...

00:48.160 --> 00:49.270
Minoru...

00:50.330 --> 00:51.490
Masao...

00:52.080 --> 00:53.360
Susumu...

00:54.330 --> 00:55.660
Yuta...

00:56.660 --> 00:57.770
Yaichi..

00:58.580 --> 00:59.910
Toyoaki...

01:00.680 --> 01:01.790
Isao...

01:02.590 --> 01:03.960
Ryosuke...

01:04.629 --> 01:05.710
Yukio...

01:06.460 --> 01:07.420
Takahiro...

01:19.360 --> 01:22.360
Master, we should go.

01:23.030 --> 01:24.940
It's not good for your health.

01:27.360 --> 01:32.220
I wonder how long I'll be able
to make the trip here.

01:38.880 --> 01:42.240
I'd like to settle the scores
for these children

01:43.160 --> 01:45.620
who died while I'm in charge.

01:47.880 --> 01:55.670
I've already received seven cases caused by demons this month.

02:00.140 --> 02:02.340
My children in the Demon Slayer Corps...

02:03.230 --> 02:08.169
are on the front lines even as we speak,
fighting the demons.

02:11.440 --> 02:14.660
No matter how many lives
the demons take...

02:54.230 --> 02:56.220
MUGEN

03:19.010 --> 03:23.340
For now, let's hide our swords on our backs.
Oh no! The train's leaving!

03:26.340 --> 03:28.060
Are the police still around?

03:28.060 --> 03:29.840
We'll have to go even if they are.

03:32.230 --> 03:34.820
I'm taking you on! Lord of this land!

03:34.830 --> 03:36.020
Hey, idiot!

03:36.410 --> 03:37.660
We should go, too!

03:39.280 --> 03:40.860
Hey, don't leave me behind!

03:44.030 --> 03:45.910
W-Wait up!

03:47.160 --> 03:49.360
Tanjiro! Inosuke!

03:49.690 --> 03:50.690
Zenitsu!

04:06.590 --> 04:07.790
So fast!

04:08.430 --> 04:09.790
Sorry! We're very sorry!

04:10.230 --> 04:12.610
Forget that! Get over here, idiot!

04:12.610 --> 04:13.810
So freakin' fast!

04:21.060 --> 04:22.720
Ma'am, is that all right?

04:23.060 --> 04:24.610
Thank you.

04:24.610 --> 04:26.060
Sorry to trouble you.

04:26.060 --> 04:26.870
Oh no.

04:26.880 --> 04:29.410
It's the least I can do.

04:39.660 --> 04:41.160
He's a Hashira, right?

04:41.410 --> 04:42.790
This Rengoku person...

04:43.730 --> 04:46.070
Are you sure you'll recognize his face?

04:46.390 --> 04:47.170
Sure,

04:47.510 --> 04:51.220
He had this gaudy hairstyle,
and I remember his scent, too.

04:51.230 --> 04:52.470
Hey!

04:52.810 --> 04:54.890
I think I'll know it's him once we get close.

04:56.480 --> 04:57.640
Delicious!

05:18.380 --> 05:28.670
DEMON SLAYER -KIMETSU NO YAIBA-
THE MOVIE: MUGEN TRAIN

05:30.290 --> 05:31.290
Delicious!

05:32.010 --> 05:32.960
Delicious!

05:34.040 --> 05:34.970
Delicious!

05:37.640 --> 05:38.970
Delicious!

05:40.480 --> 05:41.560
Delicious!

05:43.890 --> 05:45.060
Delicious!

05:46.890 --> 05:47.640
Delicious!

05:49.230 --> 05:50.060
Delicious!

05:51.460 --> 05:52.320
Delicious!

05:54.710 --> 05:55.570
Delicious!

05:57.960 --> 05:58.820
Delicious!

05:59.460 --> 06:01.120
Is that the Flame Hashira guy?

06:01.130 --> 06:02.340
- Delicious!
- Yeah.

06:02.710 --> 06:04.210
Not just some random glutton?

06:04.210 --> 06:05.820
- Delicious!
- Yeah.

06:06.380 --> 06:07.290
Delicious!

06:07.290 --> 06:09.590
Um, excuse me...

06:10.560 --> 06:11.420
Delicious!

06:11.430 --> 06:13.060
R-Rengoku?

06:13.730 --> 06:14.890
Delicious!

06:15.430 --> 06:19.140
Uh, we really get that part already.

06:26.190 --> 06:28.910
And you're the kid
from that day at the Master's.

06:29.190 --> 06:29.990
Yes.

06:30.330 --> 06:31.770
I'm Tanjiro Kamado.

06:32.190 --> 06:37.660
And they are my fellow Demon Slayers,
Zenitsu Agatsuma and Inosuke Hashibira.

06:37.990 --> 06:41.690
I see. And inside that box there...

06:42.030 --> 06:42.910
Yes.

06:43.240 --> 06:45.010
It's my sister Nezuko.

06:45.710 --> 06:48.670
Right! That demon we saw that day, huh?

06:48.680 --> 06:53.090
Since the Master's acknowledged her,
I won't say any word for now.

06:56.680 --> 06:58.340
Have a seat here.

07:05.280 --> 07:08.110
Being inside the lord is mind-blowing!

07:08.110 --> 07:11.770
You're going to break the glass!
Calm down already, will ya?

07:12.060 --> 07:14.440
What are you three doing here?

07:14.890 --> 07:16.270
A mission?

07:16.560 --> 07:18.710
We received an order from a Kasugai Crow.

07:19.040 --> 07:25.290
"The casualties of the Mugen Train are increasing.
Join Rengoku on site," he said.

07:25.660 --> 07:28.910
Yes! I see now! Understood!

07:28.910 --> 07:30.040
Right.

07:30.830 --> 07:33.070
Also, there's one more thing.

07:33.960 --> 07:36.260
Something I wanted to ask you, Rengoku.

07:37.230 --> 07:39.220
What is it? Let's hear it.

07:39.840 --> 07:41.920
About my father...

07:42.260 --> 07:43.970
What about your father?

07:44.840 --> 07:46.670
Well, he was really frail.

07:46.680 --> 07:48.010
Was he really?

07:48.440 --> 07:51.490
But even if it was cold enough
to freeze your lungs,

07:51.490 --> 07:53.190
he could still perform
a kagura dance in the snow.

07:53.190 --> 07:54.490
Well, I'm glad to hear it!

07:56.910 --> 07:57.910
The thing is...

07:57.910 --> 07:58.910
What's up?

07:59.530 --> 08:01.020
Hinokami Kagura...

08:01.580 --> 08:02.570
Dance!

08:03.610 --> 08:07.440
I suddenly found myself doing the kagura
that I'd seen as a child.

08:07.990 --> 08:11.370
If you know anything about that, Rengoku...

08:11.760 --> 08:13.760
I was hoping you'd tell me.

08:19.290 --> 08:20.210
Right!

08:21.210 --> 08:22.620
But I know nothing!

08:23.710 --> 08:26.860
I've never even heard the term "Hinokami Dance" before,

08:27.310 --> 08:32.470
But it's truly commendable that your father was able to adapt his kagura dance to battle.

08:32.809 --> 08:34.860
All right, end of discussion!

08:35.059 --> 08:36.940
Um, can you try to help me a little more?

08:37.360 --> 08:40.770
You should become my Tsuguko my apprentice! Im look after you!

08:40.780 --> 08:44.460
Hold on a second! And just what are you looking at?

08:45.410 --> 08:47.410
He's totally weird, all right.

08:47.410 --> 08:49.990
Flame Breathing has a long history.

08:50.240 --> 08:55.620
In any given era, there's always been a Flame and Water swordsman among the Hashira.

08:56.080 --> 08:57.070
Flame.

08:57.410 --> 08:58.370
Water.

08:58.790 --> 08:59.660
Wind.

09:00.080 --> 09:00.970
Stone.

09:01.310 --> 09:04.090
Thunder. Those are the fundamental
breathing techniques.

09:05.140 --> 09:08.720
The other techniques were created
as offshoots of those five.

09:09.340 --> 09:11.970
Mist is a fork of Wind.

09:12.640 --> 09:13.840
Young Mizoguchi!

09:14.180 --> 09:15.970
What color is your sword?

09:16.810 --> 09:20.110
My name's Kamado. And the color is black.

09:20.360 --> 09:21.610
A black sword, huh?

09:21.940 --> 09:23.660
Well, isn't that unfortunate?

09:25.080 --> 09:26.660
For real?

09:26.940 --> 09:30.310
I've never known a swordsman
with a black sword that became a Hashira.

09:30.530 --> 09:34.670
On top of that, I hear that they have
no clue which style to master.

09:36.680 --> 09:38.620
Come to me, and I'll train you!

09:38.960 --> 09:40.420
You can rest easy now!

09:40.680 --> 09:41.920
No, thank you!

09:41.930 --> 09:44.370
And just what are you looking at?

09:51.730 --> 09:55.270
He's strange, but he seems to be very caring.

09:55.640 --> 09:58.720
And from his scent, I can pick up his strong sense of justice.

10:01.560 --> 10:05.190
Awesome! Awesome! So fast!

10:05.440 --> 10:07.890
That's dangerous, you idiot!

10:07.890 --> 10:11.790
I'm gonna run outside
and race to see who's faster!

10:12.130 --> 10:14.710
- You can't possibly be that stupid, can you?
- That's dangerous.

10:15.790 --> 10:18.460
You never know when a demon might appear.

10:21.960 --> 10:24.960
You're kidding, right? Demons show up on this train?

10:25.840 --> 10:26.720
Sure do!

10:26.730 --> 10:27.890
What? They do?

10:27.890 --> 10:32.560
Nooo! So, we're not heading to where the demons are, but we're here?

10:32.560 --> 10:34.310
Nooo!

10:34.310 --> 10:36.060
I'm getting off!

10:36.760 --> 10:41.590
Over 40 people have disappeared on this train.

10:41.930 --> 10:46.160
The Corps sent a few swordsmen,
but then they all went silent.

10:46.580 --> 10:49.070
That's why I, a Hashira, am here.

10:54.940 --> 10:59.160
Right, I see! I'm getting off! I'm getting off!

11:07.040 --> 11:08.260
May I...

11:08.630 --> 11:09.840
see your...

11:10.430 --> 11:11.710
tickets, please?

11:13.090 --> 11:14.120
What's he doing?

11:14.710 --> 11:18.560
The conductor's going to check your ticket and punch a hole in it.

11:29.980 --> 11:30.940
Here.

11:55.310 --> 11:56.420
What is this?

11:57.060 --> 11:58.840
There's a horrible scent,

12:00.590 --> 12:02.090
Thank you...

12:02.430 --> 12:04.260
very much.

12:08.680 --> 12:09.860
Mr. Conductor...

12:10.190 --> 12:11.990
You could get hurt,
so please step back.

12:12.330 --> 12:16.490
As this is an emergency, please overlook the fact that I have a sword.

12:36.380 --> 12:40.340
Was it a Blood Demon Art that hid that massive body?

12:40.710 --> 12:42.810
I had a hard time detecting you.

12:44.310 --> 12:48.270
But if you bare your fangs
at innocent people...

12:49.780 --> 12:55.220
my bright red Flame Blade will burn you to the bone!

13:00.740 --> 13:02.460
Flame Breathing...

13:02.960 --> 13:04.460
First Form...

13:26.090 --> 13:27.090
Amazing.

13:27.430 --> 13:29.590
He sliced off the demon's head
with one blow.

13:32.930 --> 13:34.590
There's still one more.

13:34.940 --> 13:36.270
Come with me!

13:37.610 --> 13:39.570
All right!

13:40.580 --> 13:43.520
D-Don't leave me behind!

14:02.680 --> 14:05.010
You will not lay a finger on that man!

14:10.360 --> 14:11.940
Didn't you hear me?

14:12.280 --> 14:14.860
I said I'm your opponent.

14:15.230 --> 14:19.360
What the hell is it? It's got long arms!

14:19.360 --> 14:20.440
All right!

14:20.690 --> 14:22.770
- First come, first served!
- Hold up!

14:22.780 --> 14:24.810
We gotta save the passenger first!

14:24.810 --> 14:27.370
It won't matter once I destroy that thing!

14:42.410 --> 14:44.840
You'll be safe in the back of the train. Go on.

14:46.890 --> 14:48.260
We're good to go now.

14:48.640 --> 14:50.260
Let's finish him off in short order.

14:59.060 --> 15:00.360
Flame Breathing...

15:00.860 --> 15:02.360
Second Form...

15:06.190 --> 15:08.020
Rising Scorching Sun!

15:28.590 --> 15:29.540
Tha...

15:30.260 --> 15:31.540
Tha...

15:31.910 --> 15:35.470
That was awesome, Bro! Talk about brilliant sword skills, man!

15:35.980 --> 15:38.310
Please make me your apprentice!

15:38.310 --> 15:41.110
Fine by me! I'll make a fine swordsman out of you!

15:41.110 --> 15:43.110
- Me, too, please!
- Me, three!

15:43.480 --> 15:45.640
I'll train all of you!

15:45.640 --> 15:48.560
Big Bro Rengoku!

15:48.810 --> 15:50.060
Bro!

15:50.060 --> 15:52.120
- Bro!
- Bro!

15:52.490 --> 15:54.990
Big Bro Rengoku!

16:35.690 --> 16:39.360
I did as I was told! I punched their tickets and put them to sleep!

16:39.690 --> 16:43.290
Please! Put me to sleep, too, now!

16:43.630 --> 16:47.760
Please let me be reunited with my dead wife and daughter!

16:48.680 --> 16:50.420
I'm begging you.

16:50.930 --> 16:52.710
I'm begging you.

16:54.040 --> 16:55.620
Sure thing.

17:00.090 --> 17:02.110
You did a good job.

17:04.940 --> 17:06.940
Go to sleep.

17:10.060 --> 17:13.310
Have a nice dream where you can meet your family.

17:14.390 --> 17:15.609
Excuse me.

17:17.880 --> 17:20.790
What do you want us to do?

17:21.960 --> 17:25.790
Their slumber will grow deeper
in a little while.

17:26.130 --> 17:28.460
Wait here until then.

17:28.960 --> 17:35.590
Perceptive Demon Slayers sometimes wake up sensing the presence of bloodthirsty demons.

17:35.930 --> 17:41.060
When you tie the ropes, be careful not to touch their bodies.

17:42.140 --> 17:45.560
I will have to stay in the first car for a while.

17:45.890 --> 17:49.470
Hang on until everything's ready to go...

17:50.090 --> 17:52.990
so that you can have blissful dreams.

17:53.740 --> 17:55.160
Okay.

18:51.330 --> 18:54.210
What's going on? What happened?

19:00.640 --> 19:01.840
Calm down.

19:02.340 --> 19:03.720
Calm down.

19:04.810 --> 19:06.170
You have to calm down.

19:16.560 --> 19:17.570
Hey!

19:17.830 --> 19:19.570
It's Big Bro!

19:19.940 --> 19:21.740
Welcome home, Big Bro!

19:22.080 --> 19:23.660
Did you sell the charcoal?

19:41.430 --> 19:43.340
Big Bro?

19:55.110 --> 19:59.440
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm so sorry!

20:09.080 --> 20:11.910
To be able to die while dreaming...

20:12.240 --> 20:14.460
Just how lucky are you?

20:15.040 --> 20:18.820
It doesn't matter how powerful
a Demon Slayer you are.

20:19.460 --> 20:25.120
A human's driving force is the heart, the spirit!

20:27.840 --> 20:31.640
All you have to do is destroy the spiritual core.

20:31.980 --> 20:34.010
You can kill them just like that!

20:34.340 --> 20:37.310
All human hearts are the same.

20:37.930 --> 20:43.520
So fragile and weak, like glasswork.

20:45.830 --> 20:48.740
Do we tie ourselves to them by the wrist?

20:49.160 --> 20:53.070
That's right. Don't forget what he warned us about.

21:01.680 --> 21:04.420
Take a deep, slow breath...

21:05.180 --> 21:07.340
while you count.

21:09.130 --> 21:12.340
Do that, and you'll fall asleep.

21:12.710 --> 21:14.120
One...

21:14.460 --> 21:15.510
Two...

21:16.040 --> 21:17.190
Three...

21:17.860 --> 21:19.110
Four...

21:19.940 --> 21:20.940
Five...

21:21.730 --> 21:22.940
Six...

21:28.110 --> 21:32.390
And then, we were surprised because Big Bro suddenly burst into tears!

21:32.690 --> 21:34.290
What a weirdo!

21:35.790 --> 21:39.410
Oh my, you must be exhausted.

21:39.410 --> 21:42.740
It's not such a big deal, okay? I'm fine.

21:45.660 --> 21:48.320
WUR
You don't have a fever, do you?

21:48.710 --> 21:52.340
Take it easy and get some rest today okay?

21:52.980 --> 21:54.340
I'm all right.

21:54.340 --> 21:55.840
Are you sure?

21:56.590 --> 21:58.390
Hey! You come back here!

21:59.680 --> 22:01.060
Gotcha!

22:01.060 --> 22:03.220
What do you think you're doing?

22:03.680 --> 22:07.220
Hey! You stop that right now!

22:10.360 --> 22:14.020
I was having a bad dream or something.

22:16.080 --> 22:19.990
Falling deeper into sleep, deep in their dreams...

22:20.280 --> 22:23.360
Forget to breathe, deep in their dreams...

22:23.740 --> 22:27.120
And even if a demon comes,
deep in their dreams...

22:32.010 --> 22:33.540
Looks like fun.

22:33.960 --> 22:37.120
You're starting to have a happy dream, aren't you?

22:40.530 --> 22:41.870
You are falling...

22:43.110 --> 22:44.390
You are falling...,

22:45.030 --> 22:46.640
into a dream.

22:53.140 --> 22:55.140
It's a deep slumber.

22:56.390 --> 22:57.640
They can...

22:58.360 --> 23:00.740
no longer awaken.

23:00.740 --> 23:02.410
LOWER ONE

23:10.630 --> 23:11.990
This way!

23:12.410 --> 23:14.120
The peaches over here taste great!

23:14.460 --> 23:16.560
And there are tons of white clovers in bloom!

23:16.560 --> 23:18.640
I'll make you a chaplet!

23:19.010 --> 23:21.060
I can make these really great-looking ones...

23:21.560 --> 23:22.720
Nezuko!

23:23.010 --> 23:25.390
Yes! Make a lot, okay...

23:26.230 --> 23:27.760
Zenitsu?

23:34.830 --> 23:38.070
There's a river along the way,
but it's shallow, so you'll be okay, right?

23:38.410 --> 23:39.320
River?

23:41.360 --> 23:43.570
What am I going to do, Zenitsu?

23:44.160 --> 23:46.320
I can't swim.

23:46.910 --> 23:51.340
I-I'll just carry you on my back and jump right over the river!

23:52.010 --> 23:54.340
Not even your toes will get wet, Nezuko!

23:57.540 --> 23:59.840
Just leave it to me!

24:00.380 --> 24:02.340
Let's go!

24:17.480 --> 24:19.440
Expedition Team! Expedition Team!

24:19.440 --> 24:21.310
We're the Cave Expedition Team!

24:21.310 --> 24:23.220
Expedition Team! Expedition Team!

24:23.230 --> 24:25.060
We're the Cave Expedition Team!

24:25.060 --> 24:26.570
Expedition Team! Expedition Team!

24:26.580 --> 24:27.370
Boss!

24:27.740 --> 24:28.620
Boss!

24:29.290 --> 24:32.370
What's up, Underling 1 and Underling 2?

24:32.960 --> 24:37.040
I can smell the master of this cave
over there, pompoko!

24:37.630 --> 24:40.540
And I can hear it breathing
as it sleeps, squeak!

24:45.230 --> 24:47.060
Here he is!

24:47.310 --> 24:49.640
All right, let's go! Showdown!

24:49.980 --> 24:51.510
- Roger that, Boss!
- Roger that, Boss!

24:52.230 --> 24:55.090
Hey you! Come with me, Underling 3!

24:55.730 --> 24:59.340
Come over here! Look, I'll give you
these sparkly acorns! C'mon!

24:59.590 --> 25:01.440
Let's go!

25:01.780 --> 25:03.770
- Hey!
- Hey!

25:31.880 --> 25:33.540
Why did I come here?

25:37.640 --> 25:38.770
Oh, right.

25:39.110 --> 25:41.270
To report to my father...

25:41.890 --> 25:43.690
that I've become a Hashira.

26:03.490 --> 26:05.870
So what if you've become a Hashira?

26:10.680 --> 26:11.670
Worthless.

26:12.090 --> 26:13.340
It means nothing.

26:14.090 --> 26:17.340
You're never going to amount
to anything anyway.

26:18.230 --> 26:19.640
'Neither you...

26:20.090 --> 26:21.840
nor I.

26:28.160 --> 26:29.270
Brother...

26:31.080 --> 26:34.320
Was our father pleased to hear your news?
father pleased to hear your news?

26:34.610 --> 26:40.570
Do you think our father will acknowledge me
if I become a Hashira, too?

26:43.540 --> 26:45.620
He wasn't always like that.

26:46.710 --> 26:50.210
After all, he did rise to the rank
of Hashira in the Demon Slayer Corps,

26:50.960 --> 26:53.090
He was a passionate man.

26:53.510 --> 26:57.420
And yet, one day, out of the blue,
he quit being a swordsman.

26:58.460 --> 26:59.790
Suddenly.

27:00.860 --> 27:05.270
The man who'd raised us both
with such enthusiasm...

27:09.110 --> 27:10.310
Why?

27:12.860 --> 27:16.270
It's pointless to thinkote about such things, so stop.

27:17.410 --> 27:20.540
it
Senjuro is even worse off.

27:21.460 --> 27:26.370
He barely has any memories of our mother who died of illness when he was very young,

27:26.380 --> 27:28.790
and just look at the state our father is in.

27:33.960 --> 27:35.390
I'm going to be honest.

27:35.980 --> 27:38.840
Our father wasn't happy to hear it.

27:39.260 --> 27:41.510
He told me that it meant nothing.

27:41.840 --> 27:45.760
But that's not enough to extinguish my passion!

27:46.590 --> 27:49.010
This flame inside my heart
will never go out!

27:49.840 --> 27:52.020
I'll never give in!

27:52.330 --> 27:54.020
And Senjuro...

27:56.160 --> 27:58.770
You're not like me.

27:59.410 --> 28:01.240
ou have a big brother...

28:01.830 --> 28:04.270
who believes in his little brother.

28:04.910 --> 28:09.120
No matter what path you take, you're going to become a fine human being!

28:09.540 --> 28:11.540
Keep that burning passion
inside your heart!

28:11.790 --> 28:12.760
Let's do our best!

28:13.380 --> 28:14.960
Let's do our best-and live on!

28:15.590 --> 28:17.260
No matter how lonely-it-gets.

28:24.460 --> 28:25.970
Looking good.

28:26.440 --> 28:28.440
Those ropes that I created are used...

28:28.440 --> 28:32.860
for a special technique that allows one to invade
the dreams of whoever you're tethered to.

28:33.480 --> 28:38.190
I always fight with the utmost caution.

28:38.560 --> 28:43.540
Once you're asleep, Hashira or not,
you're no different than a baby.

28:44.240 --> 28:49.910
I'll enjoy the feast after killing the Demon Slayers.
